      "text": "A 50 year old woman presents with complaints of persistent fatigue, itching, and mild right upper quadrant abdominal pain. On examination, she has jaundice and hepatomegaly. Laboratory tests reveal elevated alkaline phosphatase and positive anti-mitochondrial antibodies. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
